thread.title: SA jobless rate still high

title: SA jobless rate still high
text:
Thu, Sep 10, 2015, 6:01 PM NZST - New Zealand Markets closed SA jobless rate still high AAP – 3 hours ago Print 
South Australia continues to have the worst jobless rate in the country but the state government says it takes "some comfort" from the latest figures. 
Unemployment in SA remained stable at 7.9 per cent in August despite the national rate dipping to 6.2 per cent. 
Employment Minister Gail Gago says there's still much work for the government to do but she takes some comfort from the fact that employment has been growing for the past eight months. @YahooNZBusiness on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Rivers chain cuts 130 jobs in Victoria AAP 
The Rivers clothing chain has cut 130 jobs in regional Victoria as it shuts down three of its warehouses.
